{
  "stem": "13063.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] We are coming now--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1943.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] November, 1943.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We are coming on to the year 1944.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very little.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All what the Poles, bringing raw materials to the Madritsch factory were telling us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In 1944, the Madritsch factory, which was, which was located outside the ghetto, and we were walking from the, from camp, into the Madritsch factory and back.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was about three miles each-- each way.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Madritsch factory was relocated into the camp, into the camp itself, the Plaszow, Plaszow camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At that time, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the Madritsch firm had an individual, by the name of Raimund Titsch.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Raimund Titsch, he is mentioned also in the Keneally book.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He somehow established a relationship with my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He had-- he was a nice man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was an Austrian, a Viennese.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he had great admiration for my father's perfect knowledge of German and my father's intellectual ability.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he somehow established with him a relationship of not friendship, but perhaps of some kind of admiration for the knowledge of my father.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] My father took advantage of it, took fortunate advantage of it, by asking Titsch to intercede with Oskar Schindler, to take us into his [INAUDIBLE] factory.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The, once the camp, Plaszow camp is liquidated and it is being liquidated because the Russians were coming, closer, and closer, to Krakow.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I heard that Schindler was a fine German, a good German, who took good care of his Jews, who were working at that time outside.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was like a branch of Plaszow, a branch not far from Plaszow, but about I think 2 and 1/2 miles from Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was his factory.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
